    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It is possible for the individual password stores to be encrypted, so there's no way of knowing what the key inside each file may be without decrypting it first.  And because keymanager is an interface to possibly any implementation (e.g. HSM) we'd need to consider the capabilities of the endpoint so we don't put an unreasonable burden on it (or worse, exclude some potential implementations from being able to support the interface).\r\n\r\nThis is definitely something we want, it's just a case of finding a way to make it work for both current and future key managers.",
